Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
All measured values are within or close to normal ranges, except for a mildly elevated MCHC and a markedly high platelet distribution width, which may indicate some variation in platelet size but is of unclear clinical significance in isolation. Lipid profile and blood counts are otherwise unremarkable. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected; clinical correlation is recommended.
